The paper deals with integrating an external language model into a sequence-to-sequence architecture for handwritten word recognition, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach, Candidate Fusion, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and neural networks, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach through experiments, which involves performance evaluation and comparison, making cs.IR a possible sub-category.
